result.execSummary:
The defendant Cory R Zahn was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Intimidate Witness/Threaten Force, etc. [Modifiers: Repeater], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 940.43(3).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

supervisions.notes: Consecutive to: any Wisconsin state prison sentence but concurrent to Ct. 2 in 16-CF-29.

miscConds.notes: To pay the costs of the action.   If probation is revoked or discharged with outstanding financial obligations, a civil judgment shall be entered against the defendant in favor of restitution victims and/or governmental entities for the balance due.  All available enforcement actions will be used to collect the debt.

Maintain absolute sobriety from alcohol.   Not to possess or consume any controlled substances without a valid prescription and then only take in the amount and frequency prescribed.  Not to possess or use any drug paraphernalia. No contact with the confidential informant.
Complete any counseling, evaluations, programs and assessments, including AODA assessments, as appropriate resulting from the Department's COMPAS assessment.  Maintain stable residence.

records.addlTxt: Defendant Cory R Zahn in court with attorney Brett E Reetz.  Defendant Cory R Zahn in custody.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Court reviews events in file, reviews factual errors in PSI.  State gives sentencing recommendation, makes statement. Defense gives sentencing argument. Defendant makes statement to the court.  Court makes statement, imposes sentence.

Minute sheet. State gives plea agreement.  Court questions defendant on change of plea.  Rights/elements/max. penalties reviewed with defendant.  Defendant enters no contest plea to Ct. 1.   Defense stipulates to factual basis to accept plea.  Court finds plea made freely, knowingly and voluntarily, accepts plea, and finds guilty of Ct. 1. Court dismisses Ct. 2 but reads in for sentencing.   Court reviews collateral consequences of felony conviction, possible penalties. Defendant must have a DNA sample on file with the State of Wisconsin. Court orders PSI.  Court not setting bond in this file, defendant isn't going anywhere. Sentencing hearing set for 6/21/16 at 3:30 pm.
Defense waives right to Prelim. Court questions defendant on waiver. Court finds waiver made freely and voluntarily, accepts waiver and binds over for trial. Court finds probable cause for bindover.

Defendant Cory R Zahn in court with attorney Brett E Reetz.  Defendant Cory R Zahn in custody.  Joan M. Korb appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Court reviews charge(s), max. penalties, right to counsel, right to preliminary hearing. Defense waives reading of the complaint.
